docs.abstract: The administration is proposing two waves of checks to individuals and another $500 billion for small and large businesses as part of its economic response to the coronavirus pandemic.
docs.snippet: The administration is proposing two waves of checks to individuals and another $500 billion for small and large businesses as part of its economic response to the coronavirus pandemic.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration on Wednesday broadened the government’s response to the coronavirus pandemic and spelled out the first details of a $1 trillion economic package, asking Congress for an infusion of $500 billion for direct payments to taxpayers and $500 billion in loans for businesses.

headline.main: Trump Seeks $500 Billion in Checks for Taxpayers
headline.print_headline: U.S. Seeks $500 Billion in Checks for Taxpayers

byline.original: By Nicholas Fandos and Emily Cochrane

docs.abstract: Lora Shiao will be the new acting director for the National Counterterrorism Center amid a broader reshuffling of top intelligences aides and expected personnel cutbacks
docs.snippet: Lora Shiao will be the new acting director for the National Counterterrorism Center amid a broader reshuffling of top intelligences aides and expected personnel cutbacks
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Lora Shiao, a career American intelligence officer, will be the next acting director of the National Counterterrorism Center, the government’s central clearinghouse for intelligence on terrorist threats, Trump administration officials said on Saturday.

headline.main: Top U.S. Intelligence Official Taps New Counterterrorism Chief
headline.print_headline: Top U.S. Intelligence Official Taps New Counterterrorism Chief

docs.abstract: On a conference call with the nation’s governors, President Trump said they should try to get ventilators on their own ahead of an expected crush of coronavirus cases.
docs.snippet: On a conference call with the nation’s governors, President Trump said they should try to get ventilators on their own ahead of an expected crush of coronavirus cases.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump told a group of governors on Monday morning that they should not wait for the federal government to fill the growing demand for respirators needed to treat people with coronavirus.

headline.main: Trump to Governors on Ventilators: ‘Try Getting It Yourselves’

docs.abstract: President Trump will conduct the high-profile diplomatic gathering by teleconference instead, a White House official said.
docs.snippet: President Trump will conduct the high-profile diplomatic gathering by teleconference instead, a White House official said.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Group of 7 summit will not be held as scheduled at Camp David in June but will instead be convened by teleconference because of the coronavirus outbreak, a White House official said on Thursday.

headline.main: White House to Cancel In-Person Meeting of G7, Citing Coronavirus Outbreak
headline.print_headline: In-Person Meeting of G7 Is Canceled

docs.abstract: The Trump administration released several pages of simple behaviors for keeping schools, homes and businesses safe during a coronavirus outbreak.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration released several pages of simple behaviors for keeping schools, homes and businesses safe during a coronavirus outbreak.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration on Monday night issued several pages of tips for navigating the coronavirus, organizing a set of recommendations for schools, businesses, homes and offices into a document that resembles easy-on-the-eye restaurant food-safety charts.

headline.main: Open Windows. Don’t Share Food. Here’s the U.S. Government’s Coronavirus Advice.

docs.abstract: The outbreak has closed businesses, made workers stay home and kept passengers off airplanes. That has lawmakers considering the biggest bailout in modern history.
docs.snippet: The outbreak has closed businesses, made workers stay home and kept passengers off airplanes. That has lawmakers considering the biggest bailout in modern history.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Entire sectors of the American economy are shutting down, threatening to crush businesses, put millions of people out of work and forcing lawmakers to consider a vast financial bailout that would dwarf the federal government’s response to the 2008 crisis.

headline.main: Washington Weighs Big Bailouts to Help U.S. Economy Survive Coronavirus
headline.print_headline: Weighing an Immense Bailout For Businesses, With Strings

docs.abstract: A weekend getaway at Mar-a-Lago put the president in contact with several people who later tested positive for the virus. The White House physician said the president had tested negative for the virus.
docs.snippet: A weekend getaway at Mar-a-Lago put the president in contact with several people who later tested positive for the virus. The White House physician said the president had tested negative for the virus.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The lights were low and the disco balls spinning as a cake with a fiery sparkler shooting flames into the air was brought out to a robust rendition of “Happy Birthday,” joined by President Trump. The birthday girl, Kimberly Guilfoyle, the girlfriend of Donald Trump Jr., then pumped her fist in the air and called out, “Four more years!”

headline.main: On a Saturday Night in Florida, a Presidential Party Became a Coronavirus Hot Zone
headline.print_headline: Uninvited Guest at Mar-a-Lago Birthday Party: The Coronavirus

byline.original: By Peter Baker and Katie Rogers

docs.abstract: The 100-page federal plan laid out a grim prognosis and outlined a response that would activate agencies across the government.
docs.snippet: The 100-page federal plan laid out a grim prognosis and outlined a response that would activate agencies across the government.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A federal government plan to combat the coronavirus warned policymakers last week that a pandemic “will last 18 months or longer” and could include “multiple waves,” resulting in widespread shortages that would strain consumers and the nation’s health care system.

headline.main: U.S. Virus Plan Anticipates 18-Month Pandemic and Widespread Shortages

byline.original: By Peter Baker and Eileen Sullivan

docs.abstract: Whole sectors of the United States economy have gone dark to slow the spread of the coronavirus. Here’s what comes next.
docs.snippet: Whole sectors of the United States economy have gone dark to slow the spread of the coronavirus. Here’s what comes next.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The American economy has stopped working.

headline.main: The U.S. Shut Down Its Economy. Here’s What Needs to Happen in Order to Restart.
headline.print_headline: Strategies to Restart an Economy on Ice

docs.abstract: The future role of the American Embassy in Kabul is tied to the fate of the peace process and a military withdrawal, even as violence continues.
docs.snippet: The future role of the American Embassy in Kabul is tied to the fate of the peace process and a military withdrawal, even as violence continues.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It was once a sideshow to the American military in Afghanistan and later became one of the largest diplomatic missions in the world. Now, as the United States Embassy in Kabul transitions to its newest role, its future is tied to a fragile peace process, one that will withdraw American troops even as violence continues.

headline.main: As U.S. Troops Leave Afghanistan, Diplomats Are Left to Fill Uncertain Mission
headline.print_headline: U.S. Troops’ Afghan Exit Ties Embassy’s Fate to a Fragile Peace Process
